      • exportPersistingElements

        public static ImportExport.ExportReport exportPersistingElements(CloseableIterator<? extends PersistingElement> elementsIterator,
                                                 ObjectOutputStream out)
                                                          throws IOException
        Serialize a binary representation for elements in an OutputStream. Dependencies are not serialized. Elements are removed from cache to avoid memory consumption.
        Parameters:
        elementsIterator - an iterator over the elements to be serialized ; closed by the method
        Returns:
        lastElement the last element serialized from the collection
        Throws:
        IOException

      • importPersistingElements

        public static long importPersistingElements(InputStream fis)
                                     throws DatabaseNotReachedException,
                                            IOException,
                                            ClassNotFoundException,
                                            ImportExport.ReadException
        Import a serialized set in a InputStream. Each element is loaded with data found from the input stream and stored. Elements are removed from cache to avoid memory consumption.
        Parameters:
        fis - the input stream to import from ; must support InputStream.markSupported()
        Returns:
        the number of imported elements
        Throws:
        DatabaseNotReachedException
        IOException
        ClassNotFoundException
        ImportExport.ReadException

      • readSerializedPersistingElements

        public static <T extends PersistingElement> long readSerializedPersistingElements(InputStream fis,
                                                                  Process<T> process)
                                             throws DatabaseNotReachedException,
                                                    IOException,
                                                    ClassNotFoundException,
                                                    ImportExport.ReadException
        Processes sequentially each element of a serialized stream without importing them. Each element is removed from cache as soon as it is processed so as to avoid memory consumption.
        Parameters:
        fis - the input stream of elements
        process - the process to be applied to each element
        Returns:
        the number of processed elements, including those that rose an error
        Throws:
        ImportExport.ReadException - errors while processing elements
        DatabaseNotReachedException
        IOException
